Privacy Policy
The terms 'We', 'Us', or 'Our' in this agreement refer to the development team of the apps created by
VibrantAppHub Studio
.
Protecting the privacy of our users is a top priority at VibrantAppHub Studio. Our Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and protect the personal information you provide when using our app. We are committed to ensuring the confidentiality and security of your data, and we strictly adhere to applicable privacy laws and regulations. By using our app, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy and understand how your information is handled to deliver a safe and personalised experience.
Accepting Privacy Policy and the terms of service
Before using our app, you are required to accept our Privacy Policy and Terms of Service. By doing so, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to abide by the guidelines and policies set forth by VibrantAppHub Studio. Our Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information, while our Terms of Service govern your use of the app and establish the rights and responsibilities between you and VibrantAppHub Studio. By accepting these agreements, you demonstrate your commitment to respecting our policies and ensuring a secure and enjoyable experience for all users of the app.
Changing our privacy policy and terms of service:
At VibrantAppHub Studio, we may update or modify our Privacy Policy and Terms of Service from time to time to reflect any changes in our practices or legal requirements. It is important to review these updates periodically to stay informed about any adjustments that may affect your use of our app. By continuing to use our app after changes have been made, you acknowledge and accept the revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Service. We recommend reviewing these policies regularly to ensure you are familiar with the latest terms and conditions governing your use of our app.
Privacy Policy and Disclaimer for our apps
This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect the information you provide while using our app. By accessing or using our app, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.
User-Generated Recipes:
The recipes featured on our apps are user-generated and come from our active community on Facebook(
Recipes
), submitted through emails, and uploaded via the recipe upload option on our Android/iOS apps. We take great care to review each recipe to ensure it aligns with dietary requirements suitable for individuals with diabetes. However, we cannot guarantee the accuracy, safety, or effectiveness of the recipes, as they are contributed by users.
Not a Medical App:
Our app is not a medical app, and it does not provide health or medical recommendations, calculations, references, wellness reports, or diagnoses without including the sources of the medical information. The app is designed for sharing and exploring recipes within our community.
Source of Medical Information:
Any medical information provided within the app is sourced from reputable external sources, and we make an effort to include references for transparency. However, we do not endorse any unverified health claims or propose miraculous solutions.
Community-Driven Content:
The content on our app is driven by our engaged community on Facebook and users of our Android app. We encourage users to share their experiences and insights, but it's essential to verify information independently.
Your Consent:
By using our app, you consent to the terms outlined in this privacy policy.
What is personal data?
Personal data refers to any information that relates to an identifiable individual. It includes both factual details and subjective information that can directly or indirectly identify a person. Personal data encompasses various forms, such as names, addresses, phone numbers, email addresses, social media profiles, financial information, health records, IP addresses, and any other data that can be linked to an individual's identity. It is essential to handle personal data with care and in accordance with applicable privacy laws and regulations to protect individuals' privacy and ensure the secure processing of their information.
Personal data which we handle
We only process your personal data with your consent, when it is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party, or when it is necessary for us to comply with a legal obligation. We describe below the processing of your personal data, including the specific purposes, legal basis, and storage duration.
Name:
When you sign up to our app, we may process your name based on your consent. We will retain your name as long as you have an account with us.
Email address:
We process your email address for the purpose of enabling login and creating an identity in our system. Your email address may also be used for support and marketing purposes, provided that you have given your explicit consent. Signing up to our app is optional, and any processing of your email address will be based on your consent. We will keep your email address until you delete your account and data.
Other information submitted by the user:
If you choose to upload recipes, we will store that data on our cloud database, but we will not share it with any third parties. The recipe may include images/photos and text information that you have added. We may also use your profile picture for your account. Please note that any user-generated recipe content may be displayed publicly in our app to all users. We will only process this data with your consent, and it will be kept until you delete the recipe or choose to delete your account with all associated data.
In addition, you may post reviews to recipes and add images to them. You may also post in chef communities, which are publicly visible to all users of the app. This data will also be kept until you choose to delete it or delete your account with all associated data.
We reserve the right to delete user-generated content that violates any of our policies. Users are solely responsible for the content they upload, and they should ensure that they have the necessary rights to do so. If content is found to be in violation of our policies, it may be removed. We also provide users with report options to notify us of any violations.
Deletion after inactivity
We adhere to the principle of retaining your information for no longer than necessary for the purposes for which it was collected and processed. The duration of time for which we retain your information is determined by the purposes for which we collected and used it, and/or as required to comply with applicable laws.
Permitted Users
By creating an account, you confirm that you are either 13 years of age or older, or that you have obtained permission from your legal guardian/parent to use the app. If you are unsure about whether you have reached the age of 13 or if you are unclear about this section, please seek assistance from your legal guardian or parent before creating an account. For more information about children's privacy, please refer to our Children's Privacy policy.
You may only create an account on behalf of others if you are authorized to do so as a parent, guardian, or legal representative. By creating such an account, you certify and agree that you have the authority to do so, that we are entitled to rely on your certification as true, and that you will hold us harmless from any claims by the account holder that you did not have authority to create an account on their behalf.
We reserve the right to restrict eligibility for using our app or Services, and to reject any account creation or deletion requests at our sole discretion, without incurring any liability. We will exercise this right only where we have a reasonable concern or issue.
