Subscriptions and premium accounts
Subscriptions and premium accounts paid activation of the premium account is optional. The specific characteristics of the premium account, in particular price, term and the features included in the premium account are displayed within the app.The free trial period is only valid for some particular users. If you are eligible for free trial, After the free trail period, your subscriptions will be automatically renewed and charged as per the selected plan period. You can cancel subscription at any time on Google Play and Apple App Store subscriptions page. Subscription cancellation goes into effect only after the current billing period has passed. The available payment methods depend on the users location. The additional content and functions of the premium account are digital content. The users does not acquire any property right in them, only a simple right of use limited to the term of the content or availability of the content. After the end of its term, the premium account automatically turns into a regular user account again.
How We Share and Disclose Your Information
Service Providers:
We provide access to or share your information with operations and maintenance contractors and other third parties who perform services on our behalf. They have access to perform these services but are prohibited from using your information for other purposes. They provide a variety of services to us, including billing, sales, marketing, test proctoring, product content and features, advertising, analytics, research, customer service, data storage, security, fraud prevention, payment processing, and legal services.
Protection of the app and Others:
By using the app, you agree that we may access, retain, and disclose the information we collect about you if it's necessary to comply with the law or a legal process, enforce our agreements with you, investigate potential violations of our policies, respond to claims of third-party rights infringement, respond to customer service requests, or protect the rights, property, or safety of the app, our users, or the public. This may include sharing information with other companies for purposes such as fraud prevention, spam/malware prevention, and compliance with applicable laws.
Business Transfers:
As we grow and expand our business, we may engage in partnerships, mergers, or acquisitions with other companies. In such scenarios, user information may be among the transferred assets. If any portion or all of our assets are sold or transferred to a third-party, customer information (including email addresses) may be included as part of the business assets. We will comply with any mandatory restrictions under applicable laws regarding the transfer of such information.
Related Entities and Affiliates:
We may share information with our affiliated companies that are under common ownership or control for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy.
Ads on the app:
We may share some of your information with our business partners to deliver ads that may interest you, such as your location, browser and cookie data, and usage data. Third-party ad servers or ad networks may use various technologies to compile information about your visits and usage patterns on the Service and to measure the effectiveness of their ads. However, we do not sell, rent, or share your information with these third-party ad servers or ad networks for their own marketing purposes.
You acknowledge and accept that parties with whom you share Your Data may have different privacy policies and terms of use from ours. Prior to sharing Your Data, it is your responsibility to review and accept the privacy policy and terms and conditions of any parties with whom you share Your Data, and the implications of such sharing. You agree not to hold us responsible for any use or publication of Your Data that you have chosen to share.
We will not make Your Data available to anyone without your instruction or permission, except as we state in this Policy. We reserve the right to provide any information to the authorities if we believe in good faith that we have a legal obligation to do so or if there is a threat of physical harm or other damage to you, our company, or someone else.
If we stop operating for any reason, we will notify you in advance, where possible, and allow you to delete Your Data. If we are acquired, merged, or operated by another company, that company may change this Policy or our Terms of Use, including provisions governing how it treats Your Data. You may be notified of any changes to this Policy, and if the changes are not acceptable to you, you may choose to export Your Data, close your account, and delete its contents.
Security
We take the security of Your Data seriously and have implemented measures to ensure its protection while it is within the app. When you use Services that require our employees or Service Providers to access Your Data to perform the Services, we have procedures in place to safeguard your security and privacy. However, we cannot guarantee that a breach will never occur or that Your Data will always be secure and will never be misused. You acknowledge and agree that we cannot be held responsible for any breach or unauthorized access to or use of Your Data, but we will notify users using email or other available means in case of a breach.
We offer various ways for you to share Your Data, such as email, text, other apps, and social media, which do not encrypt or protect Your Data during transmission. You understand and agree that when you use these tools, you do so at your own risk and that we cannot be held responsible for any unauthorized access or use of Your Data resulting from such sharing.
To prevent unauthorized access to Your Data, we strongly recommend that you follow best practices for safe passwords and do not share your credentials or Your Data with anyone whom you do not trust.
Service providers
Occasionally, we may establish business relationships with other companies that we believe are reliable and have confirmed that their privacy practices align with ours. These companies, which we call "Service Providers," may offer services like hosting and maintenance, data storage and management, or other types of support. To perform their duties, we only provide Service Providers with the necessary information and they are required to use reasonable security measures appropriate for the type of information involved to protect Your Data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. Our Service Providers are prohibited from using Your Data for any other purpose than what is specified by us and in compliance with our privacy policy.
